==Trivia==
*The Kraken uses the same in-game model as the [[Sea Troll Queen]] from the [[Swan Song]] quest, but recoloured. Likewise, its tentacles also use the model of the [[Tentacle (Temple Trekking)|tentacles]] encountered in [[Temple Trekking]], also recoloured.
*Its examine text and the [[jar of dirt]] are references to ''{{wp|Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest}}'' and its sequel ''{{wp|Pirates of the Caribbean: At World's End|At World's End}}''.
*The Kraken had a festive override wearing a [[santa hat]] during the [[2016 Christmas event/Gallery|2016]], [[2017 Christmas event/Gallery|2017]], [[2018 Christmas event/Gallery|2018]], [[2019 Christmas event/Gallery|2019]], [[2020 Christmas event/Gallery|2020]], [[2021 Christmas event/Gallery|2021]], [[2022 Christmas event/Gallery|2022]], [[2023 Christmas event/Gallery|2023]], [[2024 Christmas event/Gallery|2024]], and [[2025 Christmas event/Gallery|2025]] Christmas events.
*The {{WP|Kraken}} is a mythological creature originating from Norse folklore.
*According to former ''Old School RuneScape'' content developer [[Mod Reach]], the Kraken's underwhelming damage output is due to what he described as a [[game engine]] [[bug]] that, despite his protests, [[Jagex]] ultimately decided to adopt as a feature of the boss.{{CiteVideo|author=Mod Shauny|title=In the Games Industry - An interview with ex-Mod Reach!|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i55LS-y1ULg&t=9683s|timestamp=2h41m23s|date=28 January 2020|site=|notes=|name=}}
** Because of this bug, the Kraken's intended Defence level of 150 and Magic level of 390 were both set to 1.
*The Kraken was inspired by fan concepts{{CiteNews|title=DevBlog: What shall we do next|url=https://secure.runescape.com/m=forum/a=427/sl=0/forums?380,381,6,65435457|quote=Some of the ideas about a Kraken were really fun to read.|newsdate=2013-08-09}}{{CiteNews|quote=We have seen loads of really good concepts already from players, such as the Kraken|title=Dev Blog: Player made content|url=http://services.runescape.com/m=news/dev-blog-player-made-content?oldschool=1|newsdate=2013-10-18}}{{CiteNews|quote=There are numerous ideas that you have put forward to us already such as the Kraken boss|title=Dev Blog: 2014|url=http://services.runescape.com/m=news/dev-blog-2014?oldschool=1|newsdate=2014-01-07}} appearing on the official Old School Community Blog.{{CiteGeneral|author=Capt McGee|url=https://oldschoolrscommunity.blogspot.com/2013/07/the-kraken-osrs-boss.html|title=The Kraken - OSRS Boss.|accessdate=2026-02-09|date=2013-07-27}}{{CiteGeneral|url=https://oldschoolrscommunity.blogspot.com/2013/11/some-kraken-photos.html|author=Capt McGee|title=Some Kraken Photos|date=2013-11-03|accessdate=2026-02-09}} One entry from the blog was republished in the first and only edition of the Old School Community Magazine.{{CiteGeneral|title=Old School Community Magazine|url=https://viewer.joomag.com/old-school-july-2013/0169113001374750162?short&|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20221207030952/https://viewer.joomag.com/old-school-july-2013/0169113001374750162?short&|archivedate=2022-12-06|date=2013-07-28|accessdate=2026-01-11}} The original blog post detailed a three-stage battle where the Kraken would first be fought from a boat, then retreat underwater where players would don [[fish bowl helmet]]s and [[diving apparatus]]es to destroy the portal it tries to escape into, and finally players would take on the Kraken directly to kill it. Ultimately, a much simpler version of the encounter was implemented.

